  "prompt": "Why does my vagina smell fishy after intercourse and a man has ejaculated inside me?",
  "response": "A fishy smell after intercourse can be caused by a variety of factors, often related to bacterial imbalances or infections. One common cause of a fishy odor is bacterial vaginosis (BV), an overgrowth of bacteria in the vagina. Semen can alter the pH balance of the vagina, potentially exacerbating or triggering BV. \n\nOther potential causes could include:\n\n1. **Sexually Transmitted Infections (STIs)**: Certain STIs, like trichomoniasis, can cause a fishy odor.\n2. **Poor Hygiene**: Residual semen and vaginal fluids can contribute to odor if not cleaned properly.\n3. **Infrequent Changing of Menstrual Products**: If you're on your period, not changing tampons or pads frequently enough can lead to a bad smell.\n\nTo address this issue:\n\n1. **Visit a Healthcare Provider**: They can diagnose what is causing the odor and recommend appropriate treatment.\n2. **Good Hygiene Practices**: Ensure you cleanse gently but thoroughly after intercourse.\n3. **Probiotics and Diet**: Sometimes dietary changes and probiotics can help maintain a healthy vaginal flora.\n\nUltimately, seeing a healthcare professional is important to accurately diagnose and treat any underlying conditions.",
